Package: smolBayes
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Posterior Inference via Sparse Grid Quadrature Methods
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2018-12-14
Author: Joshua Hewitt
Maintainer: Joshua Hewitt <joshua.hewitt@colostate.edu>
Description: Implementation of the weighted mixtures approach for computing posterior quantities in Bayesian analyses.  The weighted mixtures approach uses sparse grid quadrature methods to assist in efficiently computing posterior quantities when the number of model parameters is large.
License: GPL-3
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
Suggests: testthat, fields
Depends: R (>= 3.0.2)
Imports: mvQuad, Rcpp, doRNG, foreach, itertools
LinkingTo: Rcpp (>= 0.12.4), RcppArmadillo, RcppEigen (>= 0.3.3.3.1)
SystemRequirements: A system with a recent-enough C++11 compiler
        (such as g++-4.8 or later).
NeedsCompilation: yes
